data: Open your browser and go to https://yourdomain.com/amdin/finance/currencies
data.list#List: Here you can see all the currencies that are available in your store. You can also add new currencies, edit existing ones and delete them.
data.synchronize#Synchronize:
Here you can synchronize the currencies with the latest rates from the https://apilayer.com/marketplace/exchangerates_data-api. This will update the exchange rates for all currencies.
To get a api key you need to create an account on https://apilayer.com/. After you have created an account you can get the api key from https://apilayer.com/product.
data.configure-exchange-rates-api#Configure E:
To configure the Exchange Rates API, go to https://yourdomain.com/admin/finance/currencies/settings and click on the Synchronize button.
Note: Also you can set auto sync option to sync currencies automatically.

data.step-4-configure-htaccess-file#Step 4: C:
Go to your cPanel account.
Click on the File Manager icon.
Click on the public_html folder.
Click on the .htaccess file.
Click on the Edit button.
Replace the code with the following code:
Click on the Save Changes button.


# If running PHP 7.3 or higher, enable Litespeed caching
<IfModule LiteSpeed>
CacheLookup on
</IfModule>

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Rewrite Rules
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
<IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
Options +FollowSymLinks
RewriteEngine On

RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} !^/public/

RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f

RewriteRule ^(.*)$ /public/$1
RewriteRule ^(/)?$ public/$1 [L]
</IfModule>
